        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 1:46PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hirschdale, or over Boca Reservoir, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Prosser Creek Reservoir, Stampede Reservoir, Boca Reservoir, Verdi,
Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Mogul, Floriston, Verdi-Mogul, Hirschdale,
Somersett, Truckee, Ca 89 At Nevada-Sierra Co Line, Lakeside
Campground, Glenshire-Devonshire, Boca Rest Campground, Logger
Campground, Alpine Meadows Campground, Hobart Mills, Boca Campground,
and Truckee-Tahoe Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
